
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `instmodsh` baraye modiriat va kar ba module-haye system dar Gentoo Linux estefade mishavad. In dastoor beheton komak mikone module-ha ro load, unload, va etela'ati dar moredeshoon be dast biarid.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `instmodsh list`  --> 📜 List kardan hameye module-haye mojood.
    🔹 `instmodsh load <module_name>`  --> 🚀 Load kardan yek module be system.
    🔹 `instmodsh unload <module_name>`  --> ⛔ Unload kardan yek module az system.
    🔹 `instmodsh show <module_name>`  --> 👀 Namayesh etela'at dar morede yek module khass.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ instmodsh list

    🔹 List kardan hameye module-haye mojood dar system.

    $ instmodsh load vboxguest

    🔹 Load kardan module `vboxguest`.

    $ instmodsh unload vboxguest

    🔹 Unload kardan module `vboxguest`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ instmodsh show nvidia

    🔹 Namayesh etela'at dar morede module `nvidia`, mesle path, dependencies va size.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `instmodsh` command is used for managing and working with system modules in Gentoo Linux. It helps you load, unload, and retrieve information about modules.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `instmodsh list`  --> 📜 List all available modules.
    🔹 `instmodsh load <module_name>`  --> 🚀 Load a module into the system.
    🔹 `instmodsh unload <module_name>`  --> ⛔ Unload a module from the system.
    🔹 `instmodsh show <module_name>`  --> 👀 Show information about a specific module.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ instmodsh list

    🔹 List all available modules on the system.

    $ instmodsh load vboxguest

    🔹 Load the `vboxguest` module.

    $ instmodsh unload vboxguest

    🔹 Unload the `vboxguest` module.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ instmodsh show nvidia

    🔹 Show information about the `nvidia` module, such as path, dependencies, and size.

